        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: use OpenSSH readiness for Tart leases",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Make Tart lease readiness use the OpenSSH/SSH-config path instead of the raw Go TCP pre-dial path.\n- Preserve Tart port 22 behavior, empty fallback ports, per-lease key handling, and the existing `uname -s && test -d ~` ready check.\n- Add focused prepareLease coverage for the readiness target construction.\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/644\n\n## Validation\n\n- `go test -race ./internal/providers/tart ./internal/cli` under the CI/default `022` umask\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- Autoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings, patch correct at 0.86 confidence\n- `CRABBOX_LIVE=1 CRABBOX_LIVE_PROVIDERS=tart scripts/live-smoke.sh` attempted with Tart 2.32.1 on Apple Silicon\n\n## Notes\n\nReported by @kmcquade in https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/issues/644.\n\nThe live smoke exercised the new OpenSSH readiness branch, but this host could not route to the guest over its Tart bridge: both host `nc` and host OpenSSH returned `No route to host`. The guest itself was healthy, had SSH listening, and could reach the host. The guarded smoke timed out and verified complete cleanup: Tart inventory and Crabbox lease inventory were both empty afterward. This does not reproduce the reporter's narrower system-OpenSSH-succeeds/raw-Go-dial-fails condition, so the reporter's successful live workaround remains the direct behavioral proof.\n",
